\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The free product 
\begin_inset Formula $G_{1}*G_{2}$
\end_inset

 combines the generators of 
\begin_inset Formula $G_{1}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $G_{2}$
\end_inset

 with no relations.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The fundamental group of joining two topological spaces at a point (or with
 the intersection being contractible) is the free product of the fundamental
 groups.
 If you go around one of the loops of a figure-eight, that doesn't commute
 with going around the other loop.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The amalgamated free product 
\begin_inset Formula $G_{1}*_{H}G_{2}$
\end_inset

 over homomorphisms 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi_{1}:H\to G_{1}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi_{2}:H\to G_{2}$
\end_inset

 combines the generators of 
\begin_inset Formula $G_{1}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $G_{2}$
\end_inset

 and adds relations: for all 
\begin_inset Formula $h\in H$
\end_inset

, we identify 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi_{1}(h)=\varphi_{2}(h)$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the application of amalgamated free products in the SvK theorem, we specifica
lly have 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi_{1}(U)*_{\pi_{1}(U\cap V)}\pi_{1}(V)$
\end_inset

